00:34:23,302 --> 00:34:26,153
Shouldn't you feel responsible?

542
00:34:26,243 --> 00:34:28,572
The journalists and I have been proposing advertisement deals...

543
00:34:28,572 --> 00:34:30,312
just as much as the Advertising Department.

544
00:34:30,313 --> 00:34:32,543
I didn't even take time off to care for my child longer.

545
00:34:32,543 --> 00:34:33,932
You should...

546
00:34:36,112 --> 00:34:37,633
if you're sure you'll be back.

547
00:34:38,512 --> 00:34:41,133
Child-rearing doesn't end with just three months,

548
00:34:41,583 --> 00:34:45,472
so if you don't come back after taking all that time off,

549
00:34:45,762 --> 00:34:47,943
you'll only be costing the company money.

550
00:34:48,293 --> 00:34:51,132
I know, sir. It's why I didn't take time off...

551
00:34:51,132 --> 00:34:52,753
even though I'm entitled to.

552
00:34:53,203 --> 00:34:54,553
You keep suggesting I shouldn't.

553
00:34:57,873 --> 00:35:00,703
Sir, no matter how hard we work,

554
00:35:00,703 --> 00:35:04,043
we can't do anything about the low birthrate or...

555
00:35:04,043 --> 00:35:05,363
Fine.

556
00:35:07,683 --> 00:35:09,162
Anyway,

557
00:35:09,382 --> 00:35:11,733
we were asked to advertise Mureung City.

558
00:35:12,523 --> 00:35:14,133
"The Baby" should take it.

559
00:35:14,652 --> 00:35:16,753
It was originally meant for "The Deco",

560
00:35:16,753 --> 00:35:19,223
but I'm only giving it to you to boost your sales,

561
00:35:19,223 --> 00:35:21,372
so do a good job on it.

562
00:35:21,922 --> 00:35:24,943
If Mureung City is pleased with the outcome,

563
00:35:25,092 --> 00:35:27,713
all the projects from local governments...

564
00:35:28,362 --> 00:35:30,883
will be turned over to "The Baby".

565
00:35:33,103 --> 00:35:35,423
Mr. Joo, my gosh. You were...

566
00:35:35,603 --> 00:35:38,423
only being hard on us to offer us this deal,

567
00:35:38,572 --> 00:35:40,332
but we were too stupid...

568
00:35:40,683 --> 00:35:42,363
to read into your intentions.

569
00:35:42,652 --> 00:35:43,733
Thank you, sir.

570
00:35:46,183 --> 00:35:48,432
It's why being in this position can get lonely.

571
00:35:57,232 --> 00:36:00,553
Seriously? What are you doing here? Go home and have fun.

572
00:36:02,103 --> 00:36:03,852
I don't feel comfortable doing so.

573
00:36:03,973 --> 00:36:05,232
That's your punishment.

574
00:36:05,232 --> 00:36:08,053
I'd rather have fun here while being uncomfortable.

575
00:36:11,273 --> 00:36:14,813
The City of Mureung has asked us to run an advertisement piece.

576
00:36:14,813 --> 00:36:17,183
You'll take the plane there and gather notes for a day.

577
00:36:17,183 --> 00:36:19,012
Other media outlets will be there,

578
00:36:19,012 --> 00:36:22,083
so make sure you come up with a piece...

579
00:36:22,083 --> 00:36:25,543
that blows the minds of the people of Mureung City.

580
00:36:26,123 --> 00:36:27,242
Who wants to go?

581
00:36:29,833 --> 00:36:32,443
My gosh. I covered 15 stories this month.

582
00:36:32,663 --> 00:36:35,203
Well, I'm going to Gangwon Province...

583
00:36:35,203 --> 00:36:36,753
to run a piece on the wholesale warehouse.

584
00:36:36,833 --> 00:36:40,452
Actually, I'd like to ask what our plans are for...

585
00:36:40,603 --> 00:36:42,193
the readers of our first issue.

586
00:36:53,422 --> 00:36:55,583
Ha Ri is terrified to fly.

587
00:36:55,583 --> 00:36:58,673
Exactly. Besides, how can she go when she's been suspended?

588
00:36:58,953 --> 00:37:01,312
She can't since she's out having fun.

589
00:37:07,203 --> 00:37:09,883
Since I've been suspended, I'll write this piece.

590
00:37:12,273 --> 00:37:13,722
I can't go.

591
00:37:14,572 --> 00:37:15,892
Why not?

592
00:37:16,012 --> 00:37:18,863
I made a drunken mistake in front of Ms. Jang.

593
00:37:21,782 --> 00:37:23,133
No way.

594
00:37:25,982 --> 00:37:27,273
You showed her your cute side?

595
00:37:36,592 --> 00:37:37,713
You idiot!

596
00:37:38,793 --> 00:37:41,653
How can you look Ms. Jang in the eyes now?

597
00:37:44,473 --> 00:37:46,492
The embarrassment might just kill me,

598
00:37:47,302 --> 00:37:48,753
but I'll try and hang in there.

599
00:37:49,143 --> 00:37:51,392
The photos are important for this piece...

600
00:37:51,612 --> 00:37:53,942
so they need an expert photographer,

601
00:37:53,942 --> 00:37:55,562
but I busted my arm.

602
00:37:55,782 --> 00:37:58,062
I can't bring in the money with a busted arm...

603
00:37:58,282 --> 00:37:59,803
which means I can't hire a freelancer.

604
00:38:00,023 --> 00:38:01,303
Unbelievable.

605
00:38:01,583 --> 00:38:04,293
- I'll have to give up the studio. - That's enough.

606
00:38:04,293 --> 00:38:06,113
I can't look Ms. Jang in the eyes anymore.

607
00:38:08,092 --> 00:38:09,443
This is all on you now!

608
00:38:16,373 --> 00:38:19,622
Mr. Nam, the photographer hasn't contacted me yet.

609
00:38:19,842 --> 00:38:21,492
Don't tell me you still haven't hired one.

610
00:38:21,503 --> 00:38:23,193
He'll be there somewhere.

611
00:38:23,373 --> 00:38:25,992
He's your partner, so look around.

612
00:38:26,683 --> 00:38:28,793
What? My partner?

613
00:38:29,282 --> 00:38:30,332
What the...

614
00:38:35,183 --> 00:38:36,403
I found him.

615
00:38:55,273 --> 00:38:56,423
Shall we?

616
00:38:56,773 --> 00:38:59,693
Why didn't you call to say you were joining me?

617
00:39:00,212 --> 00:39:01,733
We could've carpooled.

618
00:39:02,853 --> 00:39:04,932
- Do you want this? - No.

619
00:39:06,183 --> 00:39:08,872
How about buttered squid or beef jerky?

620
00:39:09,023 --> 00:39:10,242
I'm good.

621
00:39:12,192 --> 00:39:14,173
How about we grab a drink afterward?

622
00:39:14,223 --> 00:39:16,943
I like how alcohol makes you cute and sincere.

623
00:39:16,962 --> 00:39:18,443
Can't I do as I please?

624
00:39:18,732 --> 00:39:20,063
Yes.

625
00:39:20,063 --> 00:39:21,682
Correct.

626
00:39:24,072 --> 00:39:25,222
This isn't a vacation, you know.

627
00:39:25,632 --> 00:39:27,553
But it's still a trip.

628
00:39:27,773 --> 00:39:30,823
What's so bad about buying snacks and getting in the mood?

629
00:39:31,413 --> 00:39:32,722
We're even getting on a plane.

630
00:39:34,913 --> 00:39:36,963
Unbelievable. I hate planes.

631
00:39:41,123 --> 00:39:43,893
But we're not going...

632
00:39:43,893 --> 00:39:46,142
on a vacation though.

633
00:39:46,393 --> 00:39:48,673
So you don't want any snacks?

634
00:39:54,462 --> 00:39:56,082
Isn't that a bit too much?

635
00:40:03,842 --> 00:40:05,863
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.

636
00:40:06,382 --> 00:40:09,032
We welcome you on our flight.

637
00:40:09,482 --> 00:40:12,482
The flight attendants are here to make sure you have...

638
00:40:12,482 --> 00:40:14,073
- a safe journey. - Are you all right?

639
00:40:15,123 --> 00:40:17,993
I just get nervous before the plane takes off.

640
00:40:17,993 --> 00:40:20,173
I'll be fine once we're in the air.

641
00:40:22,262 --> 00:40:24,032
You're not sick or anything, right?

642
00:40:24,032 --> 00:40:25,032
- I'm good. - Thank you for...

643
00:40:25,032 --> 00:40:28,253
your cooperation and we hope...

644
00:41:36,302 --> 00:41:37,433
Hello.

645
00:41:37,433 --> 00:41:39,023
- Hello. - Hello.

646
00:41:42,743 --> 00:41:44,923
Did Ha Ri not come with you?

647
00:41:44,942 --> 00:41:47,793
Ha Ri went on a business trip to Mureung City with Mr. Han.

648
00:41:48,913 --> 00:41:51,432
To that very far city of Mureung...

649
00:41:51,612 --> 00:41:55,202
alone with Mr. Han, with no other staff members.

650
00:41:58,623 --> 00:41:59,812
They went together.

651
00:42:01,862 --> 00:42:04,543
What are they doing there, that they went...

652
00:42:05,192 --> 00:42:06,312
by themselves?

653
00:42:06,962 --> 00:42:09,682
What a load of crock.

654
00:42:13,302 --> 00:42:16,793
Ladies and gentlemen, the pilot has turned off the seat belt sign.

655
00:42:17,143 --> 00:42:20,183
However, because there may be turbulence,

656
00:42:20,183 --> 00:42:23,133
please keep your seat belts on when you are seated.

657
00:42:23,813 --> 00:42:26,112
When the seat belt light is on,

658
00:42:26,112 --> 00:42:29,773
we will not be serving food and beverages for safety reasons.

659
00:42:31,192 --> 00:42:32,943
- Oh dear. - Oh my gosh.

660
00:42:33,192 --> 00:42:34,843
Are you okay, sir?

661
00:43:27,782 --> 00:43:29,932
Maybe he could be the one...

662
00:43:31,083 --> 00:43:32,202
Is it him?

663
00:43:33,223 --> 00:43:34,673
The bus that I missed.

664
00:43:36,493 --> 00:43:37,602
This always happens.

665
00:43:37,692 --> 00:43:39,173
Especially when I'm late for an important appointment,

666
00:43:39,223 --> 00:43:41,173
the bus won't show up.

667
00:43:41,922 --> 00:43:45,312
If I hop in a cab to save time, we get stuck in traffic,

668
00:43:45,632 --> 00:43:48,063
and the bus I was waiting for...

669
00:43:48,063 --> 00:43:50,282
speeds along in the bus express lane.

670
00:43:51,433 --> 00:43:53,442
If my impatience took control,

671
00:43:53,442 --> 00:43:55,892
and made me miss a destined meeting,

672
00:43:57,572 --> 00:43:58,793
will I...

673
00:43:59,913 --> 00:44:03,233
regret not holding his hand later on?

674
00:44:18,592 --> 00:44:21,912
Why won't this open?

675
00:44:22,532 --> 00:44:23,722
Gosh.

676
00:44:25,402 --> 00:44:26,622
It opened easily.

677
00:44:27,072 --> 00:44:28,892
They made it well. You know...

678
00:44:30,072 --> 00:44:32,722
- Do you want this? - No.

679
00:44:33,183 --> 00:44:34,293
Okay.

680
00:44:37,453 --> 00:44:38,733
Sir.

681
00:44:42,953 --> 00:44:44,102
Thank you.

682
00:44:47,163 --> 00:44:50,082
I was giving you my handkerchief, not my hand.

683
00:44:51,132 --> 00:44:53,912
Yes, handkerchief.

684
00:45:03,072 --> 00:45:04,562
- What? - Hey, Ha Ri.

685
00:45:04,813 --> 00:45:06,992
Should I keep my lab coat on or take it off?

686
00:45:07,842 --> 00:45:09,662
Why are you asking me about you taking clothes off?

687
00:45:11,012 --> 00:45:13,273
- Ask the reporter there. - What?

688
00:45:13,982 --> 00:45:15,303
Both look good?

689
00:45:15,322 --> 00:45:17,303
Stop joking around. You're embarrassing me.

690
00:45:17,523 --> 00:45:20,023
Okay. Should I take the pictures with or without?

691
00:45:20,023 --> 00:45:21,843
Take it off if you want. I don't care.

692
00:45:22,793 --> 00:45:23,912
Gosh.

693
00:45:24,592 --> 00:45:26,043
It's better with it on?

694
00:45:26,333 --> 00:45:28,553
Okay, got it. Work hard.

695
00:45:29,563 --> 00:45:30,952
She says I look good with it on.

696
00:45:31,032 --> 00:45:32,753
Okay.

697
00:45:34,243 --> 00:45:35,352
Gosh.

698
00:45:37,712 --> 00:45:40,233
- Was that Dr. Yoon Jae Young? - Yes.

699
00:45:45,853 --> 00:45:47,133
What is it this time?

700
00:45:47,183 --> 00:45:49,573
Should I sit or stand for the picture?

701
00:45:49,993 --> 00:45:53,262
It would be better standing by the window looking cool. right?

702
00:45:53,262 --> 00:45:56,582
It'll bet better seated at my desk so that my nameplate shows.

703
00:45:57,732 --> 00:45:59,113
Sit for the photo...

704
00:45:59,362 --> 00:46:00,553
and cover your gut.

705
00:46:03,873 --> 00:46:06,852
Sure, got it. Okay. Work hard.

706
00:46:09,743 --> 00:46:10,892
Let's start.

707
00:46:18,012 --> 00:46:19,652
What? Why? What? What?

708
00:46:19,652 --> 00:46:21,782
Should I smile or not?

709
00:46:21,782 --> 00:46:23,353
It's best not smiling, right?

710
00:46:23,353 --> 00:46:25,742
To look serious and professional.

711
00:46:25,993 --> 00:46:27,793
No. Smiling may be better.

712
00:46:27,793 --> 00:46:29,362
This is a local hospital.

713
00:46:29,362 --> 00:46:32,213
So it'll be better to look friendly.

714
00:46:32,362 --> 00:46:34,983
Just shut your trap and take the picture, you punk.

715
00:46:40,172 --> 00:46:41,243
Okay.

716
00:46:41,243 --> 00:46:43,622
I look great both ways? What?

717
00:46:43,973 --> 00:46:45,823
Enough, Ha Ri.

718
00:46:52,482 --> 00:46:53,633
Doctor.

719
00:46:55,583 --> 00:46:57,273
It'll be this big.

720
00:46:59,253 --> 00:47:01,073
(My child whines if I don't let her watch on my smartphone.)

721
00:47:03,333 --> 00:47:04,512
That won't be easy.

722
00:47:05,893 --> 00:47:08,462
Mureung is named that because there are no royal tombs.

723
00:47:08,462 --> 00:47:10,622
In order to hide the location of the kings' graves,

724
00:47:10,902 --> 00:47:13,072
they built fake graves here.

725
00:47:13,072 --> 00:47:15,693
There is a legend that a dragon rose from there.

726
00:47:15,873 --> 00:47:18,062
So the saying goes.

727
00:47:19,143 --> 00:47:21,262
- Take all the pictures you want. - Thank you.

728
00:47:24,612 --> 00:47:25,903
Should I take some that way?

729
00:47:27,353 --> 00:47:28,403
I think it'll look good.

730
00:47:30,052 --> 00:47:31,202
Here.

731
00:47:31,453 --> 00:47:32,573
Excuse me.

732
00:47:56,953 --> 00:47:58,162
- Okay, good. - Good?

733
00:48:00,322 --> 00:48:01,472
Shall we go?

734
00:48:04,493 --> 00:48:08,362
Okay. The official schedule for the day is over.

735
00:48:08,362 --> 00:48:10,182
Feel free to take more pictures.

736
00:48:10,333 --> 00:48:13,012
If you want to hang out more, feel free to do that as well.

737
00:48:13,192 --> 00:48:14,862
Thank you, everyone.

738
00:48:14,862 --> 00:48:16,082
- Thank you. - Sure.

739
00:48:19,402 --> 00:48:22,852
Ha Ri. Don't you think we need something better for the main shot?

740
00:48:23,003 --> 00:48:26,093
Right? Should we take some pictures of the sunset?

741
00:48:32,853 --> 00:48:34,633
Is Ha Ri not back yet?

742
00:48:34,953 --> 00:48:37,303
She went to Mureung. She'll probably be home late.

743
00:48:37,322 --> 00:48:39,003
- Come eat. - Auntie.

744
00:48:39,393 --> 00:48:40,713
The photographer is a man.

745
00:48:40,762 --> 00:48:42,812
What if something happens while they're alone together?

746
00:48:43,862 --> 00:48:45,012
Like what?

747
00:48:46,563 --> 00:48:47,782
Something frightening.

748
00:48:55,143 --> 00:48:58,892
I wonder if we needed to rent a car just to go take one picture.

749
00:48:59,612 --> 00:49:01,693
You said your pride is on the line.

750
00:49:02,643 --> 00:49:04,162
It'll say, "Photo by Han I Sang."

751
00:49:04,712 --> 00:49:06,202
So my pride is on the line too.

752
00:49:07,152 --> 00:49:08,472
Even if I did refuse to do this,

753
00:49:08,623 --> 00:49:10,742
I've never given less than 100 percent.

754
00:49:12,953 --> 00:49:14,113
I know.

755
00:49:16,362 --> 00:49:17,943
Will we have enough time?

756
00:49:22,732 --> 00:49:24,883
We can make our flight if we rush.

757
00:49:25,503 --> 00:49:26,622
Okay.

758
00:50:04,873 --> 00:50:07,693
How about this for your explanation of Mureung City?

759
00:50:17,123 --> 00:50:18,273
What?

760
00:50:19,552 --> 00:50:22,412
You're the first photographer to takes pictures...

761
00:50:23,123 --> 00:50:24,582
with the article in mind.

762
00:50:28,762 --> 00:50:29,883
It's perfect.

763
00:50:32,802 --> 00:50:35,193
- Should we take a few more? - Okay.

764
00:50:37,273 --> 00:50:39,463
She went there for work. What could possibly happen?

765
00:50:39,572 --> 00:50:43,363
She went on multi-day business trips with men, and nothing happened.

766
00:50:43,583 --> 00:50:45,403
What if something happens this time?

767
00:50:45,953 --> 00:50:48,303
You've heard of incidents like that.

768
00:50:48,552 --> 00:50:50,702
You work like crazy and miss the train.

769
00:50:50,853 --> 00:50:53,202
You look for a place to stay, and there's only one.

770
00:50:53,322 --> 00:50:56,512
Furthermore, they have one vacant room.

771
00:50:57,333 --> 00:51:00,753
I hate these cliche and offensive things...

772
00:51:01,232 --> 00:51:02,402
so much.

773
00:51:02,402 --> 00:51:05,983
Why couldn't she come home just because there's no train?

774
00:51:06,632 --> 00:51:09,693
- Right? - Unless there is a rainstorm...

775
00:51:09,902 --> 00:51:11,093
What?

776
00:51:17,753 --> 00:51:18,963
It looks like rain.

777
00:51:19,512 --> 00:51:20,673
Rain?

778
00:51:23,223 --> 00:51:25,052
They can't go anywhere, and it's raining.

779
00:51:25,052 --> 00:51:27,073
Their clothes are drenched, and they become chilly.

780
00:51:27,192 --> 00:51:29,623
And the boiler at the inn is broken.

781
00:51:29,623 --> 00:51:31,232
They need to be in a situation where they can't help...

782
00:51:31,232 --> 00:51:32,833
but share each other's body temperature.

783
00:51:32,833 --> 00:51:36,383
That's when something will finally happen. You know nothing.

784
00:51:39,203 --> 00:51:40,622
I don't even want to think about it.

785
00:51:58,892 --> 00:52:00,342
Our flight got canceled.

786
00:52:01,512 --> 00:52:03,313
The express bus drivers are on a strike,

787
00:52:03,314 --> 00:52:04,965
and the train tickets are all sold out.

788
00:52:07,512 --> 00:52:08,602
What should we do?

789
00:52:10,521 --> 00:52:12,432
We'll just have to borrow the car for a bit longer.

790
00:52:12,851 --> 00:52:14,372
We can't take the plane home anyway.

791
00:52:15,052 --> 00:52:16,671
Do you think we'll be able to go home?

792
00:52:16,862 --> 00:52:19,841
As long as the road doesn't get blocked due to a landslide,

793
00:52:20,121 --> 00:52:21,341
we'll be able to go home.

794
00:52:21,532 --> 00:52:22,812
Don't worry.

795
00:52:28,771 --> 00:52:31,471
We have breaking news. Due to the heavy rain in the southwest,

796
00:52:31,471 --> 00:52:33,961
a landslide has occurred in Mureung City...

797
00:52:34,112 --> 00:52:36,112
which ended up blocking the nearby coastal road.

798
00:52:36,112 --> 00:52:38,842
The authorities have sent people to urgently clear up the road,

799
00:52:38,842 --> 00:52:42,001
and they announced that it'll take around six hours.

800
00:52:42,081 --> 00:52:43,621
We will update you...

801
00:52:43,621 --> 00:52:45,181
- as soon as we hear more. - She can't be there, right?

802
00:52:45,181 --> 00:52:46,731
- We will move onto the next news. - No way.

803
00:52:53,322 --> 00:52:55,611
How is this even possible?

804
00:52:56,092 --> 00:52:58,352
How can this happen?

805
00:52:58,462 --> 00:53:00,012
It's like someone planned this.

806
00:53:00,771 --> 00:53:03,082
