830
00:54:02,362 --> 00:54:05,711
You saw the map as well. This was the only bed and breakfast.

831
00:54:05,862 --> 00:54:08,001
Exactly. It's weird that you drove to a place...

832
00:54:08,001 --> 00:54:11,292
where there's only one bed and breakfast.

833
00:54:15,442 --> 00:54:16,662
Is no one here?

834
00:54:17,242 --> 00:54:18,731
Are you here...

835
00:54:19,541 --> 00:54:23,001
to stay the night?

836
00:54:25,121 --> 00:54:26,731
Yes, we're here to stay the night.

837
00:54:28,621 --> 00:54:30,962
I bet she'll say there's only one room left.

838
00:54:30,962 --> 00:54:33,111
There are three rooms.

839
00:54:34,331 --> 00:54:36,611
But do you only need one room?

840
00:54:38,661 --> 00:54:40,921
You can rent an entire annex.

841
00:54:42,072 --> 00:54:44,101
We'll... We'll pay for the annex.

842
00:54:44,101 --> 00:54:46,251
We'll take a room each.

843
00:54:46,402 --> 00:54:49,062
And she'll even use the extra room.

844
00:54:49,742 --> 00:54:52,512
We'll sleep separately...

845
00:54:52,512 --> 00:54:54,332
and make sure we don't even touch.

846
00:54:56,251 --> 00:54:59,901
Do as you wish.

847
00:55:00,221 --> 00:55:01,901
Okay. Thank you.

848
00:55:02,192 --> 00:55:03,242
Thank you.

849
00:55:08,161 --> 00:55:10,732
I guess we need to use that to cook our own rice.

850
00:55:10,732 --> 00:55:12,060
I guess so.

851
00:55:12,061 --> 00:55:15,021
But do you think you can sleep here?

852
00:55:15,371 --> 00:55:17,051
I'll just sleep in the car.

853
00:55:17,701 --> 00:55:20,321
- No, I'll sleep in the car. - Here.

854
00:55:22,311 --> 00:55:24,091
You can change into this.

855
00:55:25,482 --> 00:55:26,961
Okay.

856
00:55:27,652 --> 00:55:28,932
You're so kind.

857
00:55:30,451 --> 00:55:31,631
We'll get changed.

858
00:55:35,422 --> 00:55:37,972
- The phone is turned off. - Ha Ri isn't home yet.

859
00:55:38,692 --> 00:55:39,822
Her phone's turned off as well.

860
00:55:39,822 --> 00:55:42,582
She told me she's low on battery. She can't come home tonight.

861
00:55:42,692 --> 00:55:43,881
She's going to sleep outside?

862
00:55:44,802 --> 00:55:46,452
She's with Mr. Han, isn't she?

863
00:55:47,371 --> 00:55:50,722
Are you going to let your daughter spend the night with a guy?

864
00:55:50,842 --> 00:55:53,122
You should go there and drag her home.

865
00:55:53,911 --> 00:55:56,562
I'm actually glad that my daughter's spending the night with a guy.

866
00:55:57,041 --> 00:55:58,691
What kind of guy is he?

867
00:55:58,842 --> 00:56:00,911
Is he normal? How old is he? Does he have his own house?

868
00:56:00,911 --> 00:56:02,001
Is he diligent?

869
00:56:04,382 --> 00:56:07,271
He doesn't own anything, and he's very old.

870
00:56:07,451 --> 00:56:10,372
On top of that, he looks very scary. He has really dark skin.

871
00:56:11,462 --> 00:56:13,312
He's a weirdo. I don't like him.

872
00:56:14,092 --> 00:56:16,082
Then why don't you marry Ha Ri?

873
00:56:18,762 --> 00:56:21,802
I'm just worried about her like an older brother.

874
00:56:21,802 --> 00:56:23,021
Don't take it out on me.

875
00:56:24,201 --> 00:56:26,691
An older brother, my foot. You were born a month later.

876
00:56:26,802 --> 00:56:30,421
Wait until she comes home. I'll teach that brat a lesson.

877
00:56:33,982 --> 00:56:35,702
The phone doesn't work here.

878
00:57:33,871 --> 00:57:37,231
I Sang, you're like a country boy.

879
00:57:37,242 --> 00:57:38,932
What are you talking about?

880
00:57:39,181 --> 00:57:42,162
People think I'm from abroad. They call me Kevin.

881
00:57:42,851 --> 00:57:43,972
Daniel.

882
00:57:44,121 --> 00:57:45,231
Sure.

883
00:57:54,992 --> 00:57:57,452
